This paper focuses on the performance analysis of small cell networks with idle mode capability, which is a key feature in wireless communication networks. The paper considers a realistic path loss model that incorporates both line-of-sight and non-line-of-sight transmissions, which suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. The paper also analyzes the coverage probability, area spectral efficiency, and energy efficiency performance, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of the idle mode capability on network densification, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of approximate expressions and upper and lower bounds, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses interference and energy consumption, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category.
